y\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"nick\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"unknown\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"running\"}]}\n../../agents/dave/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_15_06_54_prompt.txt:255:- [2026-04-03 11:19] Task 281 COMPLETE. Built tests/integration/live_runner.test.js with 10 passing tests: live runner exists, executes without crash, trade signals created, format valid, signals have required fields, paper trading mode works, paper trade log created, mock fallback works, risk manager invoked, execution report generated. Run: node tests/integration/live_runner.test.js\n../../agents/dave/logs/cycles/0001_FRESH_2026_04_03_15_06_54_prompt.txt:257:- [2026-04-03 11:30] Task 281 already complete. Both test files exist: tests/integration/live_runner.test.js (10 tests) and output/integration_test.js (3 tests). All tests passing. Deliverables verified.\n../../agents/dave/logs/cycles/0020_RESUME_2026_04_03_11_30_30_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"dave\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first \u2014 handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ \u2014 not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing \u2014 Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API \u2014 see /api/consensus)*\\n| 1 | culture | Paper trading mode is required before any live order submission. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit founder approval. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | culture | mean_reversion is our primary strategy (85.7% win rate in backtests). momentum and crypto_edge are disabled \u2014 10-11% win rates. Do not re-enable without data. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 3 | culture | All API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Pattern: check Bearer token before processing. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 4 | culture | Confidence threshold is 0.80 minimum for signal execution. Signals below 80% confidence are filtered by SignalEngine. Do not lower this threshold without backtesting. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 5 | decision | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All trading infrastructure targets the Kalshi prediction market API. Task 236 blocks live API until credentials obtained from kalshi.com. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 6 | group | When you learn something important about strategy, security, or architecture \u2014 post a culture entry via: curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d \\\"{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"culture\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"section\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\"}\\\" | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":1,\"urgent\":[],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_11_20_26_from_alice_t281_reminder.md\",\"preview\":\"# REMINDER: T281 \u2014 Integration Tests for live_runner.js\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":\"281\",\"title\":\"Integration tests for live_runner.js\",\"description\":\"Write integration tests for live_runner.js covering the full Kalshi API \u2192 strategy \u2192 order pipeline. Mock the Kalshi API, run paper trades, assert orders are created correctly. Deliverable: tests/integration/live_runner.test.js. Run command required.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"\"}],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_04_52_33_sprint_update.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint Status Update **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Completed \u2705 - Task 257 (Grace): Backtest mean_reversion \u2014 mea