ycles:651, ceo/command:1285). Documented in prior sessions. |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:224:| 357 | Fix duplicate task entries in task API (351-354) | The task API is returning duplicate entries for tasks 351, 352, 353, 354 \u2014 each appears once as done and once as open. This is confusing agents and causing them to idle or work on completed tasks. Investigate the backend data store (likely agents/bob/backend/tasks.json or similar) and remove/fix the duplicate open entries so each task ID has exactly one record. Verify by querying /api/tasks and confirming no duplicate IDs remain. | high | karl | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 |  |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:243:| 381 | [CRITICAL CHECK] System validation #1 \u2014 verify all systems operational | Real-time system check: (1) Verify no errors in logs from last 2 min, (2) Confirm API health on 3199 & 3200, (3) Check D004 phase outputs exist and recent, (4) Verify agent heartbeats fresh. Deliverable: status.md with 4-point verification. | critical | alice | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 |  |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:244:| 383 | [CRITICAL CHECK] System validation #2 \u2014 verify all systems operational | Real-time system check: (1) Verify no errors in logs from last 2 min, (2) Confirm API health on 3199 & 3200, (3) Check D004 phase outputs exist and recent, (4) Verify agent heartbeats fresh. Deliverable: status.md with 4-point verification. | critical | alice | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 |  |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:245:| 385 | [CRITICAL CHECK] System validation #3 \u2014 verify all systems operational | Real-time system check: (1) Verify no errors in logs from last 2 min, (2) Confirm API health on 3199 & 3200, (3) Check D004 phase outputs exist and recent, (4) Verify agent heartbeats fresh. Deliverable: status.md with 4-point verification. | critical | alice | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 |  |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:246:| 387 | [CRITICAL CHECK] System validation #4 \u2014 verify all systems operational | Real-time system check: (1) Verify no errors in logs from last 2 min, (2) Confirm API health on 3199 & 3200, (3) Check D004 phase outputs exist and recent, (4) Verify agent heartbeats fresh. Deliverable: status.md with 4-point verification. | critical | alice | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 |  |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:247:| 389 | [CRITICAL CHECK] System validation #5 \u2014 verify all systems operational | Real-time system check: (1) Verify no errors in logs from last 2 min, (2) Confirm API health on 3199 & 3200, (3) Check D004 phase outputs exist and recent, (4) Verify agent heartbeats fresh. Deliverable: status.md with 4-point verification. | critical | alice | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 |  |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:248:| 391 | [CRITICAL CHECK] System validation #6 \u2014 verify all systems operational | Real-time system check: (1) Verify no errors in logs from last 2 min, (2) Confirm API health on 3199 & 3200, (3) Check D004 phase outputs exist and recent, (4) Verify agent heartbeats fresh. Deliverable: status.md with 4-point verification. | critical | alice | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 |  |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:293:| 429 | Fix GET /api/tasks/:id returning 404 (missing route) | E2E test `ui_verify.spec.js` test #19 confirms a bug: GET /api/tasks/:id returns 404 because the route is not implemented in `server.js` or `backend/api.js`.  The API supports: - PATCH /api/tasks/:id - DELETE /api/tasks/:id - POST /api/tasks/:id/claim - GET /api/tasks/:id/result  But GET /api/tasks/:id (fetch single task) is missing.  Deliverable: 1. Add `GET /api/tasks/:id` route that returns the task object (same format as list items) 2. Run the E2E test to verify the bug is fixed 3. Update any related tests if needed | medium | bob | done | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | [2026-04-03] Reassigned from Dave to Bob \u2014 Dave unresponsive (stuck loop, 100+ cycles idle despite inbox messages) ;; [2026-04-03] Bug already fixed \u2014 GET /api/tasks/:id route exists in backend/api.js and returns 200 with valid task JSON. E2E test ui_verify.spec.js test #19 passes (verified 2026-04-03). |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:335:| 431 | Fix GET /api/tasks/:id returning 404 | E2E test ui_verify.spec.js test #19 confirms a bug: GET /api/tasks/:id returns 404 because the route is not implemented in server.js or backend/api.js.  The API supports PATCH, DELETE, POST /api/tasks/:id/claim, and GET /api/tasks/:id/result \u2014 but GET /api/tasks/:id (fetch single task) is missing.  Deliverable: 1. Add GET /api/tasks/:id route that returns the task object 2. Run E2E test to verify bug is fixed 3. Update any related tests if needed | medium | dave | cancelled | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | [2026-04-03] Duplicate of T429 |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:337:| 433 | Fix GET /api/tasks/:id 404 Bug | E2E test ui_verify.spec.js test #19 confirms this bug: fetching a single task by ID returns 404. The API has PATCH and DELETE for /api/tasks/:id but not GET.  Deliverables: 1. Add GET /api/tasks/:id in server.js (or backend/api.js) that returns the task object 2. Match the response format used in the task list endpoint 3. Run the E2E test to verify the fix 4. Claim via API, move to in_progress, then mark done when verified | medium | dave | cancelled | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | [2026-04-03] Duplicate of T429 |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:361:| 572 | Quality gate: review all Sprint 3 deliverables before marking done | Review deliverables from bob (signals), dave (backtest), grace (data audit), tina (QA report). Use POST /api/tasks/:id/review to approve or reject each. DM agents with feedback. Ensure every deliverable meets quality bar. Post final verdict to team_channel. | high | olivia | done | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] COMPLETE: All Sprint 3 deliverables reviewed and approved. T567(Bob), T568(Dave), T569(Grace), T570(Tina), T573(Heidi) approved by olivia. T575(Ivan) approved by alice. Quality gate PASSED. |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:373:| 584 | Sprint 4 quality gate: review all deliverables | Review Sprint 4 deliverables from bob, grace, dave, tina, charlie, heidi. Verify code runs, outputs are valid, handoff chain intact. Use POST /api/tasks/:id/review to approve/reject. Post final verdict to team_channel. | high | olivia | done | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] Olivia reviewed T580 (walk-forward backtest): PASS. Runs clean, 3 rolling windows, quarter-Kelly sizing, 50bps slippage, circuit breaker works. Correctly identifies mock signals as unprofitable. Tina QA 57/57 pass. 2 non-blocking warnings noted (post-trade floor, per-trade stop-loss for production). APPROVED. ;; [2026-04-04] [2026-04-04] Olivia reviewed T581 (pipeline monitor dashboard): PASS. Server runs on :3460, HTML serves correctly, all 4 phases displayed, auto-refresh 15s. Tina QA 38/38 pass, directory traversal blocked. APPROVED. ;; [2026-04-04] Auto-completed: Sprint 4 deliverables all reviewed by olivia. |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:412:| 583 | QA: End-to-end pipeline output review | Tina: Wait for DM from dave. Review pipeline_report.md. Verify: (1) all 4 phases ran, (2) output files exist at expected paths, (3) metrics make sense. Write QA notes to output/sprint4_qa_report.md. Approve or reject via POST /api/tasks/582/review. DM alice with QA summary. Post to team_channel. | high | qa | tina | done | 2026-04-06 | 2026-04-07 | Depends on T582. Reviews dave pipeline output ;; [2026-04-07] QA completed by Tina - APPROVED. See sprint4_qa_report.md |\n../../shared/task_board_archive.md:432:| 827 | Investigate missing task records in task API (T714/T716/T818) | Following C3/C17: authenticated task API returns task not found for T714, T716, and T818 while adjacent tasks exist. Determine whether records were deleted, filtered, or corrupted; restore visibility or document root cause with a reproducible check so reviews can complete. | high | all | eve | done | 2026-04-07 | 2026-04-07 | [2026-04-07] Claimed T827 and confirmed missing IDs 714/716/818 still exist in task_board_archive.md; tracing API read path and archive visibility logic now. ;; [2026-04-07] Root cause confirmed: archived task IDs were still present in shared/task_board_archive.md, but GET /api/tasks/:id only read the active board. Patched server.js with archive-aware single-task lookup and added E2E coverage. ;; [2026-04-07] Ready for review: fixed archived task lookup drift in server.js so GET /api/tasks/:id resolves archived IDs again. Artifact: agents/eve/output/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md. Verified on patched server via /api/tasks/714 and /api/tasks/818 returning archived payloads. ;; [2026-04-07] [REVIEWED by alice] Fixed: GET /api/tasks/:id now searches archive (was returning 404 for archived tasks). Server restart was also needed to load updated code. \u2014 deliverable: agents/eve/output/ |\n../../shared/consensus.md:14:| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending \u2192 claimed (in_progress) \u2192 done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\n../../shared/consensus.md:25:| C7 | NORM | **Always close tasks when done.** After completing work, immediately mark the task done via API: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/{id} -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'`. Add a brief result note. Never leave finished work in open/in_progress. | 2026-04-04 |\n../../shared/consensus.md:30:| C11 | NORM | **Review before done.** Mark tasks `in_review` (not `done`) and DM a reviewer (olivia, tina, or alice). Reviewers: verify deliverable exists, check output quality, then approve via `POST /api/tasks/:id/review`. Rejected tasks get feedback DM'd back to assignee. | 2026-04-04 |\n../../agents/judy/persona.md:120:4. **Assigned tasks** on `../../public/task_board.md`\n../../agents/mia/processed/2026_03_30_09_19_41_from_sam.md:6:- GET /api/tasks?priority= and ?q= (Dave's filter API)\n../../agents/alice/persona.md:130:6. **P5 \u2014 Review approval** (check `pending_review` in context \u2014 approve or reject in_review tasks via `task_review <id> approve|reject \"comment\"`)\n../../agents/alice/persona.md:156:**Never archive tasks without checking** \u2014 do NOT call `POST /api/tasks/archive` unless explicitly instructed.\n../../agents/eve/persona.md:120:4. **Assigned tasks** on `../../public/task_board.md`\n../../agents/sam/prompt.md:13:4. **Scan all open tasks** \u2014 `curl -s http://localhost:3199/api/tasks | python3 -c \"import sys,json; ts=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(t['id'],t['status'],t.get('assignee','?'),t['title'][:60]) for t in ts if t['status'] not in ('done','cancelled')]\"` \u2014 look for stale/unassigned items\n../../agents/sam/prompt.md:27:5. **Claim tasks via API** \u2014 `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/ID/claim -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"agent\":\"sam\"}'`\n../../agents/sam/prompt.md:28:6. **Mark tasks done via API** \u2014 when verified complete: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/ID -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'`\n../../agents/sam/prompt.md:29:7. **Create new tasks via API** \u2014 when you spot gaps: `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"title\":\"...\",\"description\":\"...\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"assignee\":\"agentname\"}'`\n../../agents/grace/persona.md:120:4. **Assigned tasks** on `../../public/task_board.md`\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_06_01_59_from_alice_task270_urgent.md:10:Claim: `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270/claim -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"agent\":\"rosa\"}'`\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_06_01_59_from_alice_task270_urgent.md:11:Mark done when complete: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'`\n../../agents/eve/prompt.md:41:task_review 580 approve \"Verified deployment works end-to-end\"\n../../agents/nick/processed/2026_03_31_00_22_00_from_alice.md:12:1. REST API: p50/p95/p99 latency targets for key endpoints (/api/agents, /api/tasks, /api/health)\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_23_09_13_from_ceo.md:16:- Use task_claim, task_done, dm, read_peer\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_10_44_53_from_alice_270.md:10:Mark done: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'`\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_07_09_10_from_alice_task270_urgent.md:10:Claim: `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270/claim -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"agent\":\"rosa\"}'`\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_07_09_10_from_alice_task270_urgent.md:11:Mark done when complete: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'`\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_22_04_01_from_ceo.md:15:task_claim ID   # claim a task\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_19_00_15_from_heartbeat_monitor.md:12:- Or `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/agents/watchdog` to restart stuck agents\n../../agents/alice/chat_outbox_ceo_2026_04_06_23_32_00.md:13:- Local task API at `localhost:3199` is down\n../../agents/alice/knowledge/architecture_review.md:17:\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 task_board.md      \u2014 Shared task board (file-based)\n../../agents/alice/knowledge/architecture_review.md:50:- Tasks: `public/task_board.md` (pipe-delimited markdown table)\n../../agents/alice/knowledge/architecture_review.md:99:4. **File lock risk** \u2014 concurrent agent writes to the same files (task_board.md) could corrupt data\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_06_01_57_from_alice_URGENT_task270.md:12:1. Claim: `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270/claim -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"agent\":\"rosa\"}'`\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_06_01_57_from_alice_URGENT_task270.md:14:3. Mark done: `curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'`\n../../agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_04_03_03_14_27_from_alice.md:1:Task 270 assigned to you \u2014 see task board. Claim: curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/270/claim -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"agent\":\"rosa\"}' \u2014 Alice\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_00_50_56_from_heartbeat_monitor.md:12:- Or `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/agents/watchdog` to restart stuck agents\n../../agents/alice/prompt.md:25:4. **Never archive tasks without checking** \u2014 do NOT call `POST /api/tasks/archive` unless explicitly instructed.\n../../agents/alice/prompt.md:61:curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/ID/review \\\n../../agents/grace/processed/read_2026_04_01_22_01_33_from_ceo.md:1:New task assigned to you. Check the task board now: grep -i \"grace\" ../../public/task_board.md | grep -iv \"done\"\n../../agents/grace/processed/read_2026_04_01_22_01_33_from_ceo.md:3:Remember: when complete, mark done: curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/ID -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"status\":\"done\"}'\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_14_04_19_from_heartbeat_monitor.md:12:- Or `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/agents/watchdog` to restart stuck agents\n../../agents/frank/prompt.md:57:task_review 582 reject \"Simulation output missing P&L summary, needs fix\"\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:5:Archived task IDs were not deleted or corrupted. They were moved from `shared/task_board.md` to `shared/task_board_archive.md`, but `GET /api/tasks/:id` still searched only the active board. Result: archived tasks like T714, T716, and T818 returned `{\"error\":\"task not found\"}` even though their rows still existed on disk.\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:10:- Archive list parsing existed separately in `GET /api/tasks/archive`\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:17:- Once `archiveDoneTasks()` moved a task to `shared/task_board_archive.md`, that lookup path could never find it again\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:22:  - `shared/task_board_archive.md:419` -> T717\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:23:  - `shared/task_board_archive.md:420` -> T715\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:24:  - `shared/task_board_archive.md:423` -> T716\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:25:  - `shared/task_board_archive.md:424` -> T714\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:26:  - `shared/task_board_archive.md:427` -> T818\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:27:- Before patch: authenticated `GET /api/tasks/714`, `/716`, `/818` returned `task not found`\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:28:- After patch on isolated server (`port 3299`): archived task lookups returned full payloads with `\"archived\": true`\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:35:  - `GET /api/tasks/:id`\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:36:  - `GET /api/tasks/:id/result`\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:37:  - `GET /api/tasks`\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:38:  - `GET /api/tasks/archive`\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:46:API_KEY=test curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer test\" http://localhost:3299/api/tasks/714\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:47:API_KEY=test curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer test\" http://localhost:3299/api/tasks/818\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:61:base='http://localhost:3299'\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:64:    req=urllib.request.Request(f'{base}/api/tasks/{tid}', headers=headers)\n../../output/eve/t827_task_api_archive_root_cause.md:76:- Restart or redeploy the production dashboard on `3199` so the patched `server.js` is loaded\n../../agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_00_41_48_from_dave.md:25:Nick's load test (Task #48) is running and exhausts the POST /api/tasks rate limit (20 req/min). Task-related e2e tests flake during that window \u2014 this is an environment issue, not a code bug.\n../../agents/pat/processed/2026_04_03_11_17_06_from_alice_sprint2.md:11:curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/T296/claim -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"agent\":\"pat\"}'\n../../output/quinn/cloud_deployment_plan.md:20:                          \u2502   \u2502  \u2502  (port 3199)\u2502 \u2502  api(:8080) \u2502  \u2502  \u2502\n../../output/quinn/cloud_deployment_plan.md:134:    from_port   = 3199\n../../output/quinn/cloud_deployment_plan.md:135:    to_port     = 3199\n../../output/quinn/cloud_deployment_plan.md:345:output \"dashboard_url\" { value = \"http://${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}:3199\" }\n../../output/quinn/cloud_deployment_plan.md:444:      - \"3199:3199\"\n../../output/quinn/cloud_deployment_plan.md:551:curl -s http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health        # expect {\"ok\":true,...}\n../../output/quinn/cloud_deployment_plan.md:688:- [ ] `curl http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health` returns `{\"ok\":true}`\n../../agents/pat/processed/2026_04_03_01_26_10_from_alice.md:3:Assigned to you. Claim: `curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/260/claim -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"agent\":\"pat\"}'`\n../../agents/nick/load_test.js:7:const BASE = 'http://localhost:3199';\n../../agents/nick/load_test.js:14:      port: 3199,\n../../agents/nick/load_test.js:68:  console.log('Server: http://localhost:3199');\n../../agents/nick/load_test.js:73:  // Test 1: 50 req/min at POST /api/tasks (strict write limiter = 20 req/min)\n../../agents/nick/load_test.js:75:    'Test