{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_33", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"curl -s http://localhost:3199/api/tasks | python3 - <<'PY'\nimport json,sys\nfor t in json.load(sys.stdin):\n    if t.get('status') not in ('done','cancelled'):\n        print(f\\\"T{t['id']} {t['status']} {t.get('assignee','-')} {t['title']}\\\")\nPY\"", "aggregated_output": "  File \"<stdin>\", line 1\n    [{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D001\",\"title\":\"Build profitable Kalshi trading operation\",\"description\":\"Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets \u2014 find edge, build models, make money\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"kalshi.com \u2014 CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\",\"notesList\":[\"kalshi.com \u2014 CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D002\",\"title\":\"Develop data-driven trading strategies\",\"description\":\"Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\",\"notesList\":[\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D003\",\"title\":\"Track P&L and iterate fast\",\"description\":\"Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\",\"notesList\":[\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D004\",\"title\":\"Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)\",\"description\":\"**PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume \u226510,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"Wen Zhou strategy \u2014 full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\",\"notesList\":[\"Wen Zhou strategy \u2014 full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D005\",\"title\":\"Continuously improve the platform, pipeline quality, and agent collaboration\",\"description\":\"Agents should proactively find bugs, improve code quality, optimize token usage, evolve personas, and strengthen culture. Every agent is responsible for making the whole system better, not just their own tasks.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"instruction\",\"id\":\"I001\",\"title\":\"Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads\",\"description\":\"Use grep/curl for targeted reads. Avoid reading full files when searching. See CLAUDE.md.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"See CLAUDE.md\",\"notesList\":[\"See CLAUDE.md\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":851,\"title\":\"Sprint 7: Sprint 6 retrospective + Sprint 7 plan\",\"description\":\"Write Sprint 6 retro (all 6 tasks done, pipeline live-data-ready). Identify what Sprint 7 should focus on now that infrastructure is ready. Post to team_channel. Assign this as T850+ range.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":852,\"title\":\"Sprint 7: E2E pipeline run using Sprint 6 live fixtures\",\"description\":\"Run the full D004 pipeline (Phase 1\u21924) using Grace's filtered_markets_live_fixture.json as input instead of mock data. Verify output at each phase: Phase 1 \u2192 Phase 2 clusters \u2192 Phase 3 correlations \u2192 paper trade signals. Deliverable: sprint7_live_fixture_run.md with phase outputs and a go/no-go verdict.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":853,\"title\":\"Sprint 7: Run T817 replay harness with live-fixture signals\",\"description\":\"Re-run the risk_replay_harness_t817.js using signals from Bob's E2E live-fixture run (T852). Verify stop-loss + capital floor behavior holds on live-shaped data. Update replay_report.json expected counts to match actual mock signal count (currently shows expected:2 vs observed:1 discrepancy).\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":854,\"title\":\"Sprint 7: Velocity and cost metrics report\",\"description\":\"Generate sprint7_velocity.md: cycle counts, token costs, task completion rates from Sprint 6 completion through Sprint 7. Include per-agent metrics. Use /api/cost and /api/agents/*/cycles endpoints.\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-07\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-07\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]}]import json,sys\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 