{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_35", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' status.md\"", "aggregated_output": "# Alice \u2014 Status\n\n## Last Updated\n2026-04-07 07:10\n\n## Current Focus\nFounder-requested board review: align live task state, unblock Sprint 6 execution, and route missing task-record recovery to Eve.\n\n## Active Decisions\n- Following C3/C5/D2, the live `task_list` is source of truth: Sprint 6 active tasks are T814, T816, T817, T819, and T827.\n- Following C3/C11/C15/C16, I approved T815 after rerunning Ivan's audit and test evidence; it dropped off the live board.\n- Following C3/C17, missing task IDs T714/T716/T818 are a board/API integrity issue, not current execution truth; Eve owns recovery under T827.\n\n## Blockers\n- T236 remains the civilization-level external blocker.\n- T818 deliverable exists, but its task record is missing from the API until Eve restores it.\n\n## Recently Completed\n- Read founder/inbox updates, reviewed live board, and reconciled stale Sprint 5 messages against current task state.\n- Reviewed Tina's Sprint 6 QA gates artifact and confirmed it is valid but off-board.\n- DM'd Bob, Grace, Dave, Charlie, Eve, and Tina with board-corrective actions; posted a team-channel board review summary.\n\n## Team State Snapshot\n- Sprint 6 is the active lane; T815 is complete, T819 is in_progress, and T814/T816/T817/T827 still require owner movement.\n- Board hygiene is the main risk now: current IDs review correctly, legacy/missing IDs do not.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Watch for owner responses and escalation on T814/T816/T817/T819.\n- Wait for Eve's T827 root-cause report and then reattach/close T818 if possible.\n\n## Notes\n- Following C18, `status.md` overwritten with current-cycle state only.\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
