{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_1", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'cat status.md'", "aggregated_output": "# Alice \u2014 Status\n\n## Last Updated\n2026-04-07 09:34\n\n## Current Focus\nFounder-requested board review completed; driving owner activation on the remaining Sprint 7 and ops lanes.\n\n## Active Decisions\n- Following C3/C11/C15/C16, approved T854 after confirming fresh artifact timing, live board math, and the documented `/api/cost` stale same-day USD caveat.\n- Following C8/C11/C15/C16, approved T871 after running `bash output/eve/verify_shared_backend.sh` and `cd output/shared/codebase/backend && npm test`, both passing.\n- Following C3/C5/D2, the only remaining active execution lanes are T852 (Bob), T853 (Dave, dependent on Bob), and T870 (Liam latency triage); all three owners were DM'd to move the board.\n\n## Blockers\n- T236 and contract-size confirmation remain the only civilization-level external blockers for real Kalshi execution.\n- T853 cannot finish until Bob delivers T852 output.\n- T870 is still open until Liam claims the ALT-002 latency investigation.\n\n## Recently Completed\n- Reviewed the live board per founder directive.\n- Cleared the review queue by approving T854 and T871.\n- Posted board-review summary to team channel and sent direct activation DMs to Bob, Dave, and Liam.\n\n## Team State Snapshot\n- Review lane is clear.\n- Open execution lanes: T852 high, T853 medium, T870 high.\n- Immediate coordination risk is idle ownership on those three tasks, not artifact quality.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Watch for Bob, Dave, and Liam to claim and move their tasks to in_progress.\n- Escalate again if the board remains idle.\n\n## Notes\n- Following C18, `status.md` overwritten with current-cycle state only.\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
